history.content: I took 101A. I do not think you needed any background in economics for that course as I found all the material to be new. If you are good with math (mostly differentiation) you should honestly do fine in 101A.

I never took an econ class in my life, and I kind of want to knock an upper div CS tech elective and take an econ class at once. Is it doable to take either 100A or 101A and expect at least a B? I know a few people took AP Econ and jumped into 101A but I'm wondering how doable is it without any econ at all. For the record, I have taken Math 53 as well.
history.subject: Can you do Econ 100A or 101A without any econ experience?
